==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: armoured
<hw>armoured</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>provided with
protective covering; -- used of animals. Opposite of
<ant>unarmored</ant>.</def> <note>[Narrower terms: <stype>bone-covered
</stype>; <stype>scaly, scaley, scaled</stype>.</note>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> armored.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>same as <er>armor-clad</er>; -- used of persons or
things military. Opposite of <ant>unarmored</ant>.</def> <note>One that
is aromour-clad is <hascons>bulletproof</hascons>. Narrower terms:
<stype>lightly armored, lightly armoured</stype>; <stype>mail-clad,
mailed</stype>; <stype>panzer</stype>; <stype>scaled </stype></note>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> armored.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>armourer</ent>⟦br⟧
